# Implementation Plan: Supabase Integration & Auto-Migration Layer

This plan outlines the integration of **Supabase** as the primary cloud database, alongside a **hybrid fallback & auto-migration engine**. This ensures that progress currently stored in your browser's `localStorage` is safely migrated to the cloud without any data loss, and that the app is robust enough to run locally or on Vercel seamlessly.

## User Action Required (To Activate Supabase)

To get started, you will need to create a free database project on Supabase and provide your connection keys. You can do this at any time, and the app will continue to run safely in local storage mode until you do.

### 1. Create a Supabase Project
1. Go to [supabase.com](https://supabase.com) and create a free account.
2. Click **New Project** and name it (e.g., `Interview-Coach`).
3. Set a database password and select a region closest to you.

### 2. Run Database Schema Script
Once your project is ready, go to the **SQL Editor** tab in your Supabase dashboard, paste the following SQL script, and click **Run**:

```sql
-- Create the profiles table matching our frontend typescript interfaces
create table if not exists profiles (
  username text primary key,
  cf_handle text,
  lc_handle text,
  streak integer default 0,
  last_active_date text,
  xp integer default 0,
  solved_list text[] default array[]::text[],
  solved_puzzles text[] default array[]::text[],
  solved_sql text[] default array[]::text[],
  solved_custom_count integer default 0,
  solved_puzzle_answers jsonb default '{}'::jsonb,
  solved_sql_answers jsonb default '{}'::jsonb,
  activity_log jsonb default '{}'::jsonb,
  timed_sessions jsonb default '[]'::jsonb,
  updated_at timestamp with time zone default timezone('utc'::text, now())
);

-- Enable Row Level Security (RLS) or leave it open for simple public access
alter table profiles enable row level security;

-- Create a simple policy to allow public read/write access for this demo anonymous key
create policy "Allow public access" 
on profiles for all 
using (true) 
with check (true);
```

### 3. Add Connection Keys to `.env.local`
In your local root directory (`c:\Users\Akshay\OneDrive\Documents\Antigravity\Interview-Coach`), create a file named `.env.local` and paste your project keys:
```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anonymous-anon-public-key
```
*(You can retrieve these keys in Supabase by going to **Project Settings** -> **API**).*

